&ldquo;What opportunities can’t I see because they’re not prestigious enough?&rdquo;
&ldquo;You don&rsquo;t really outperform your peers with quality per se, you outperform your peers by finding underpriced quality that others don’t judge to be valuable.&rdquo;
Girard&rsquo;s philosophy teaches us that the world is filled with under-priced opportunities that are only available to people who are comfortable with promising, but low-status projects.
The modern world rejects imitation in favor of originality at all costs.
